S application template built on the LAMP stack with jQuery and Bootstrap 5, designed to accelerate the development of team collaboration and task management applications. This template provides essential SaaS functionality including user authentication, role-based access control, team management, and three core productivity modules: Todo Lists, Kanban Boards, and Calendar with appointments.\n    11→\n    12→## Executive Summary\n    13→\n    14→### Purpose\n    15→Provide a reusable SaaS template that enables developers to:\n    16→- Rapidly deploy team collaboration applications using proven PHP/jQuery architecture\n    17→- Implement secure user authentication and authorization with PHP sessions\n    18→- Build task management systems with multiple views (List, Kanban, Calendar)\n    19→- Enable team-based workflows and collaboration\n    20→- Create scalable multi-team architectures\n    21→- Customize and extend for specific business needs\n    22→\n    23→### Key Features\n    24→- Secure PHP-based authentication system\n    25→- Role-based access control (User, Group Admin, Global Admin)\n    26→- Team management and collaboration\n    27→- Todo list with jQuery-powered interactions\n    28→- Kanban board with jQuery UI drag-and-drop\n    29→- Calendar with jQuery datepicker integration\n    30→- Interactive dashboard with Chart.js\n    31→- Responsive Bootstrap 5 design\n    32→- AJAX updates using jQuery\n    33→\n    34→## User Roles & Permissions\n    35→\n    36→### 1. Global Administrator\n    37→**Primary Users**: System administrators, platform owners\n    38→\n    39→**Permissions**:\n    40→- Full system access and control\n    41→- Manage all users across all teams\n    42→- Create and delete teams\n    43→- Assign Group Admins\n    44→- Access all team data and tasks\n    45→- System configuration and settings\n    46→- View global analytics and reports\n    47→- Manage user roles and permissions\n    48→- Access audit logs\n    49→\n    50→**Restrictions**:\n    51→- None - complete system access\n    52→\n    53→### 2. Group Administrator\n    54→**Primary Users**: Team leaders, department managers\n    55→\n    56→**Permissions**:\n    57→- Manage team members (add/remove users)\n    58→- Create and assign tasks to team members\n    59→- Manage team-specific settings\n    60→- View all team tasks and progress\n    61→- Edit/delete any task within the team\n    62→- Create team projects and categories\n    63→- Export team data and reports\n    64→- Manage team calendar events\n    65→\n    66→**Restrictions**:\n    67→- Limited to assigned teams only\n    68→- Cannot create new teams\n    69→- Cannot assign Global Admin role\n    70→- Cannot access other teams' data\n    71→\n    72→### 3. Standard User\n    73→**Primary Users**: Team members, individual contributors\n    74→\n    75→**Permissions**:\n    76→- Create personal tasks\n    77→- View and edit assigned tasks\n    78→- Update task status and progress\n    79→- Add comments and attachments\n    80→- View team calendar\n    81→- Create personal appointments\n    82→- Access team Kanban board\n    83→- View team dashboard\n    84→\n    85→**Restrictions**:\n    86→- Cannot add/remove team members\n    87→- Cannot delete other users' tasks (unless assigned)\n    88→- Limited to team-assigned projects\n    89→- Cannot modify team settings\n    90→\n    91→## Functional Requirements\n    92→\n    93→### 1. Authentication & User Management\n    94→\n    95→#### 1.1 User Registration & Authentication\n    96→- **Registration Features**\n    97→  - Email-based registration with PHP validation\n    98→  - Email verification using PHP mail functions\n    99→  - Secure password requirements (PHP password_hash)\n   100→  - Profile setup wizard with jQuery steps\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"973da573-9d24-4a54-952f-81c0a7f290fa","uuid":"39770c2f-5b7f-4882-90c3-2d41869baafb"},{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_01WPb64nCd9ztTsYX2kJi9cc","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"claude-opus-4-1-20250805","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SS2a7zHfS4DNnEKFQBZvoN","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/var/www/html/dashboard.php"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1194,"cache_read_input_tokens":17636,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1194,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":62,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"973da573-9d24-4a54-952f-81c0a7f290fa","uuid":"287538b9-a8ac-4e8d-97c8-9a80830a6e84"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SS2a7zHfS4DNnEKFQBZvoN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?php\n     2→require_once 'includes/session.php';\n     3→require_once 'includes/auth.php';\n     4→\n     5→// Require login\n     6→require_login();\n     7→\n     8→// Get current user\n     9→$user = get_current_user();\n    10→?>\n    11→<!DOCTYPE html>\n    12→<html lang=\"en\">\n    13→<head>\n    14→    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    15→    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    16→    <title>Dashboard - SaaS Template</title>\n    17→\n    18→    <!-- Bootstrap 5 CSS -->\n    19→    <link href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    20→\n    21→    <!-- Bootstrap Icons -->\n    22→    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.0/font/bootstrap-icons.css\">\n    23→\n    24→    <style>\n    25→        .navbar {\n    26→            box-shadow: 0 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,.08);\n    27→        }\n    28→\n    29→        .sidebar {\n   